                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Kinetic, Italian firm in technology pact
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Sulajja Firodia Motwani and Stefano de Marchis, director of FGT India, in New Delhi on Thursday. Picture by Ramakant Kushwaha                                   
	New Delhi, July 1: Indias Kinetic Group and Italys FGTecnopolo have formed a joint venture to offer engineering services such as design, consultancy and back-up support to infrastructure firms.         
	Kinetic Groups engineering services arm  Kinetic Communications  has formed the 50:50 venture with FGTecnopolo that will cater to SEZs, urban townships, airports, seaports, railway stations and other public or private works in the area of infrastructure, retail and hospitality.         
	The new venture, to be named Kinetic FGTecnopolo, will set up an engineering centre in Pune.         
	India is on an unprecedented path of growth and over the next 10 years, there will be tremendous growth in infrastructure, construction, retail and hospitality industry, said Sulajja Firodia Motwani, director, Kinetic FGT.         
	The company will also venture into newer areas such as traffic management systems and LED solutions.         
	The infrastructure and construction industry in India is worth Rs 5,17,000 crore.                                                                                                                                       
